# Architecture Decision Record

When adding a new architecture pattern or changing an existing one, preserve explicit decision history.

## Rules

- Document meaningful architecture choices in `docs/`.
- Prefer one focused document per topic rather than one giant architecture file.
- Update docs when code changes invalidate previous architecture guidance.
- Explain not just what was chosen, but why and what tradeoffs were rejected.

## Decisions That Must Be Documented

- CQRS/messaging changes
- aggregate boundary changes
- eventing patterns
- repository/interface direction
- exception/result strategy
- Doctrine modeling rules
- framework integration decisions such as Messenger or EventDispatcher usage
